This is the walkthrough of how to set up the SMTP server on a Linux box.
SMTP stankds for Simple Mail Transfer Protocol and has been around a long time.


First, start with a fresh Kali box
Run 
$ sudo apt-get update
and then 
$ apt-get upgrade
This updates the package list with the latest available versions and then updates the package list with the latest available versions

Next, you'll need to install postfix to host your own mail server
this is done with 
$ apt install postfix
Make sure you run it as root




